1. e4 {In 1884 the magazine "Vsemirnaia Illiustrazia", in which the chess
column was held by Chigorin himself, organized a correspondence chess
tournament. There were 12 participants, each playing two game with everyone
else. The tournament was easily won by Chigorin with 20 wins and 2 draws, 4
points ahead of the runner up. The games were then published, and the
following game started a lot of lively discussions in the press in many
countries.} 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 {The Evans Gambit} 4... Bxb4 5.
c3 Bc5 6. O-O d6 7. d4 exd4 8. cxd4 Bb6 9. Nc3 {This simple developing move
was Chigorin's favourite one and proved to be the right one.} ({The Pawn push} 
9. d5 {
often played by Anderssen, would have given good possibilities to black after}
9... Na5 10. Bb2 Ne7 {Now it would be a mistake} 11. Bxg7 Rg8 12. Bf6 Nxc4 13.
Qa4+ Qd7 14. Qxc4 {for} 14... Rxg2+ 15. Kh1 {
(if King would have taken the Rook, it would have been mated in six)} 15... Qh3
16. Nbd2 Bg4 {with a tremendous attack.}) 9... Na5 {Now, however, this Knight
jump near the fence is not so good and makes a lot of troubles to its
conductor.  Right was 9... Bg4 10. Bb5 Kf8 (!) 11. Be3 Nge7 and Black would
have kept his extra pawn and a solid position.} 10. Bg5 Ne7 11. Nd5 f6 12. Bxf6
{A risky decision. Against Steinitz our hero played the stronger move 12.Bf4.}
12... gxf6 13. Nxf6+ Kf8 14. Ng5 {The cavalry is sent audaciously to the
attack. (Different times, different spirit, different phylosophy of the game!)}
14... Ng8 ({The following continuation would have lead to a draw:} 14... Nxc4
15. Qh5 Kg7 16. Qf7+ Kh6 17. Qh5+ {Of course, in such position, it is easy to
be tempted to continue the attack, but... one should be 100% sure that it will
evolve in a win, or the material advantege could be decisive for Black.}) 15.
Ngxh7+ Kg7 16. Bxg8 Rxh7 17. Nxh7 {Urusov is now facing a difficult choice.}
17... Qh4 (17... Qxg8 18. Ng5) (17... Kxg8 18. Qh5) 18. Qf3 Kxg8 19. Nf6+ Kg7
20. Nh5+ Kg6 ({Deserved some consideration} 20... Kg8) (20... Kh6 {
would have been completely wrong because of} 21. Qf8+ Kxh5 22. Qh8+ Kg5 23. f4+
) 21. Nf4+ Kh7 22. Nd5 Be6 23. Nxb6 axb6 24. d5 Bg8 25. Rac1 Qe7 (25... c6 26.
e5 dxe5 27. Qf5+ Kh8 28. Qxe5+ Kh7 29. Rc3) 26. Qh3+ {Black, aware that it is
impossible to prevent the Rook in c1 from entering the battle via c3 with
deadly effects, resigns.} 1-0

