{BRAIN DAMAGE "I like to do the evil! I enjoy to see someone suffer". I heard
this overturning confession one evening during the supper from a chess player,
a master. I knew him in the hotel that gived hospitality to us and to the
tournament he partecipated to."Please, I beg You, don't joke! - I said and I
remained with the fork lifted - I don't know what to say and even not what to
think." "But I don't joke at all - he went on seriously and looking me in the
eyes. I feeled that he didn't lie - You have to know that I don't like to
smoke, the smokers disturb me. I don't drink and the alcoholized disgust me, I
don't take drugs and I shoul kill all those who take drugs against a wall. I
don't look for sex and I wish that all gays and perverted will take the AIDS
illness. As you can see I also don't eat so much."He keeped silence for a
while and then he asked me suddenly: "Do you smoke, drink, have sex with more
than one woman?" "...No... - I replied a little perplexed and I tried to give
to my voice an appearance of truth. I was so in trouble that I nearly
suffocated by the bit I was eating - but I cannot hide that I have a liking
for the good-looking girls. I..." "It doesn't matter, if they are serious. -
He stopped me abruptly and then he went on, and his hands played nervously
with the knife, part of the meal cover - You see, I know, to do the evil to
our next is a fault, but I cannot correct myself. It is too strong for me. If
I only could be unpunished... but I fear the consequences." I don't hide the
fact that I feeled a little worried and that at the same time I could not
disjoin my eyes of his hands that continued to play with the knife. I am not a
timorous but... I feared that his brain had "some weak fields" and I began to
believe that it should be better if place a psycanalist was listening to him
instead of me. I was on my guard. He did not perceive my uneasiness and he
went on: "The chess saved me from the jail. May be you cannot believe it, but
this is really so. It has been a fortune to meet this play. When I did
understand its nature I falled headlong in it and I become a master in little
time. I succeed in collecting here all my murderous libido and now I feel I am
quite in balance. Did you never have strange inclinations? Light mental
derangements?" "I... really... don't know.... " By listening to him I stopped
to eat and my meal become cold. I continued to turn my eyes from his face to
his hands and I did not know what to answer. I began to sweat and he gets me
out of trouble: "Don't answer me. In any case you should not be sincere." He
turned the eyes down and began to torment with the point of the knife the poor
beefsteak on his plate. Then he went on: "I need to play every day and I need
every day a victim. Of course I cannot always win and the day I lose my game
in the tournament, I play other "friendly" game with whoever, until I win and
have my gratification." I thought: "Friendly games?" I interrupted him: "What
happened today?" I was of course interested to know his answer. "It was great,
great!" I heaved a sigh of relief. Then he draw out of his jacket a little
pocket chess-board: "Do you want to see the game of today?" I did not dare say
no. "You can see - he went on - what this game means to me." I was happy to
see him to lay down the knife and I keep silence. He arranged the pieces and
began to repeat the game moves by hearth, telling me the story.} 1. d4 f5 2. e4
{"When this is possible, I always choise to play a gambit, because I find
often in it the ideal arm to give vent to my instinct. For example here I
sacrifice a pawn and I gain a very good position. 2...} 2... fxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4.
Bg5 b6 {"If my opponent had played 4...c6 it was better for him.} ({
The move is better than....} 4... d5 5. Bxf6 exf6 6. Qh5+ {e 7.Qxd5.}) 5. f3
Bb7 {"I realized suddenly the first weaknesses of the black play and I
perceived the initial shadow of pleasure that comes when I have in front of me
my "victim". 5...e3 was much better!} ({Invece... Instead} 5... exf3 {
" to my favor I had...} 6. Nxf3 Bb7 7. d5 $1) 6. fxe4 Nxe4 7. Nxe4 Bxe4 8. Nf3
Qc8 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Qa6 $2 {"The attempt to simplify the game with the
proposal to alter immediately the Queens, corrobatd my opinion. My victim
strartet to get frightened and this gave me my first "enjoyment". It should
have played 10...Qb7 to obtain a more steady defence.} 11. Qe4 $1 {
"This is the right answer to those who have fear. What a delight for me! 11...}
11... Nc6 12. d5 Na5 13. Ne5 {" I obtained more and more space and my
adversary began to be in difficulty. 13...} 13... d6 $2 {"I knew it! I knew
that the fear should obtenebrate his thoughts and that so he started to do
those little mistakes without those it is not possible to win. And if those
mistakes are not small, but great, then it is possible to inflict heavy
strokes that are so painful but that give me such a pleasure." I looked to my
speaker, he went on to describe his play. I tried to understand the deepness
of his feelings, more than the game itself. By repeating the moves of his play
of some hours ago, he lived intensely another time, here, on the table, in
this moment, all the perverted feelings he had. It was terrible to see his
eyes injected with blood. It was frightful to hear the sound of his voice that
became be hoarse. His hands moved themselves nervously and I feeled how they,
together with his voice, transmitted me a part of his hate and illness that
guided his thought. He did not show me a game, he described me an execution,
an assassination. Without corporal violence, without blood and... without law
punishment. I became fascinated... like in front of a cobra when he stand up
in front of you, ready to deliver a mortal bite. May be that I was feeling
exactly the same thing of his adversary. May be that also he had "seen" and
