hoping to exploit Black's centralised king. Both plans are promising.} 5. Bxc6
dxc6 6. Nxe5 ({Capablanca prefers the positional continuation:} 6. O-O) ({
A more modern interpretation of this plan would be} 6. d3 {
keeping open the option of casting queenside.}) 6... Nxe4 7. Nxe4 Qd4 8. O-O
Qxe5 9. Re1 Be6 10. d4 Qf5 ({After} 10... Qd5 {
